            <biogHist>
                <p>John MacNeil was born to Galleon and Marion née MacNeil, presumably in Barra. In
                    the 1841 census, John lived in Brevig on Barra and was classed as a tinker; he
                    is recorded married to Rachel née Gilles with five children: Mearon (12), Mary
                    (10), Eliza (5) Neil (2) and Peggy [Margaret] (4 months). By the 1851 Census,
                    John and Rachel had moved to Earsary, with Elizabeth, Neil and Margaret present
                    in the house. John was now crofting two acres. He was still on Earsary by the
                    1861 Census, with his daughters Mary, Elizabeth and Margaret. By 1871 John was
                    now blind and living with his wife in a house with one window. Both he and his
                    wife were now paupers. </p>
                <p>John MacNeil died in June 1874 from old age; the death certificate was signed by
                    his daughter Margaret.</p>
                <p>MacNeil was visited by Carmichael and he recited the song 'Is Toileom S Toileam'. </p>
